# Copy to infra/.env and fill in real values before running `cdk deploy`.
# These are passed as plain environment variables to the Lambda function /
# Fargate task — fine for sandbox testing. Production deployments should use
# Secrets Manager with a runtime-fetch pattern instead.
#
# AWS credentials for CDK itself (AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID / AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY)
# are NOT listed here — configure them via `aws configure` or by exporting
# them in your shell before running deploy commands.

# ── Database ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Neon connection string — sslmode=require is mandatory for Neon
DB_URL=postgresql://user:password@ep-xxx.us-east-1.aws.neon.tech/dbname?sslmode=require

# ── Auth ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Secret used to sign JWTs — generate one with: openssl rand -base64 32
AUTH_SECRET=replace-with-a-long-random-string

# ── Storage (S3) ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# The CDK stacks automatically grant the Lambda execution role / Fargate task
# role s3:PutObject and s3:DeleteObject on this bucket — no static AWS
# credentials are needed at runtime.
S3_BUCKET=my-manguito-sandbox-bucket
AWS_REGION=us-east-1

# ── Cloudinary (optional) ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Only needed when manguito.config.ts uses createCloudinaryAdapter. Passed
# through to Lambda/Fargate only when set; harmless alongside the S3 vars.
# CLOUDINARY_CLOUD_NAME=your-cloud
# CLOUDINARY_API_KEY=...
# CLOUDINARY_API_SECRET=...

# ── CORS ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Set to your frontend origin in production; * is fine for sandbox testing
ALLOWED_ORIGIN=*
